ABUJA –  Lagos on Friday continued to maintain its unenviable status as the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria as the country moved close to hit the 4,000 mark in confirmed COVID-19 cases. The total figure for Nigeria as at Friday night is 3,912 confirmed COVID-19 cases. According to the daily update by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 386 new cases on Friday out of which Lagos reported 176, followed by Kano with 65 new cases.Katsina and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) had 31 and 20 respectively. The full report reads: 386 new cases of #COVID19; 176-Lagos65-Kano31-Katsina20-FCT17-Borno15-Bauchi14-Nasarawa13-Ogun10-Plateau4-Oyo4-Sokoto4-Rivers3-Kaduna2-Edo2-Ebonyi2-Ondo1-Enugu1-Imo1-Gombe1-Osun 3912 cases of #COVID19 in NigeriaDischarged: 679Deaths: 117 ABUJA - Lagos, the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on Saturday got observers worried as both cities recorded new infections in huge numbers.According to the report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 220 new cases out of which Lagos and… May 3, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - The COVID-19 situation in Kano State took a dangerous dimension on Friday as the state for the second day topped Lagos, the epicentre of the pandemic in Nigeria. Out of the 238 new cases announced by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), Kano recorded 92 new cases… May 1, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Lagos State, the Federal Capital Territory, Kano and Oyo have spiked the number Nigeria's confirmed Coronavirus cases with the addition of 35 confirmed infections as at late Thursday night.Lagos State has 19 new infections with FCT contributing nine. Kano and Oyo have five and two new cases respectively… April 16, 2020 In "Top Stories"